&quot;A Thousand Miles&quot; is the first single from the album &quot;<a title="Vanessa Carlton - Be Not Nobody" href="http://www.last.fm/music/Vanessa+Carlton/Be+Not+Nobody" class="bbcode_album">Be Not Nobody</a>&quot;.  Some older live recordings, and a tape demo recording are named as &quot;<a title="Vanessa Carlton &ndash; Interlude" href="http://www.last.fm/music/Vanessa+Carlton/_/Interlude" class="bbcode_track">Interlude</a>&quot; with slightly different lyrics.
 The song features prominently in the 2004 movie White Chicks, starring Shawn and Marlon Wayans as FBI agents who go undercover as white girls. Speaking with <a href="http://www.songfacts.com/detail.php?id=2387" rel="nofollow">Songfacts</a> about its use in the film in a 2011 interview, Carlton said: &quot;I thought it was hilarious. Those guys are really nice, too. I ran into them backstage or something, and they asked me if they could use it. They're like fans, they're so cute. But the scene that was in was hilarious.&quot; 

